<subSubSection id="C34F12C8FFD1FA64D9FF39B8FC5F6F44" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BEA4143FFD1FA64D9FF39B8FE806CAC" blockId="34.[189,310,403,429]" box="[189,310,403,429]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<heading id="D0A2F62FFFD1FA64D9FF39B8FE806CAC" bold="true" box="[189,310,403,429]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B9219D51FFD1FA64D9FF39B8FE806CAC" bold="true" box="[189,310,403,429]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA4143FFD1FA64D9FF39E8FC5F6F44" blockId="34.[189,1399,450,582]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<taxonomicName id="4C553AC0FFD1FA64D9FF39E8FE776CDD" authorityName="Ardi" authorityYear="2015" box="[189,449,450,476]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="simolapensis">
<emphasis id="B9219D51FFD1FA64D9FF39E8FE776CDD" box="[189,449,450,476]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Begonia simolapensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
grows sympatrically on limestone with 
<taxonomicName id="4C553AC0FFD1FA64DAEA39E8FB986CDD" authorityName="Ardi" authorityYear="2015" box="[936,1070,450,476]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="olivacea">
<emphasis id="B9219D51FFD1FA64DAEA39E8FB986CDD" box="[936,1070,450,476]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">B. olivacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described above and has a similar habit (growing flat against the substrate) and leaf shape; it differs in having larger (5–9.5 × 
<quantity id="4CADECA6FFD1FA64D9FF3A23FEAF6F22" box="[189,281,520,547]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" unit="cm" value="6.0" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="4.0">4–8 cm</quantity>
, not 2.7–4.5 × 
<quantity id="4CADECA6FFD1FA64D8933A23FDEF6F22" box="[465,601,520,547]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.15" metricValueMax="3.7" metricValueMin="2.6" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" unit="cm" value="3.15" valueMax="3.7" valueMin="2.6">2.6–3.7 cm</quantity>
), glossier leaves which are a nearly uniform deep green (not olive green with paler variegation) and longer, denser hairs on the petioles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34F12C8FFD1FA64D9FF3A46FD496FB4" box="[189,767,621,694]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="etymology">
